            "text": "LionsBayHouseConcerts: Stephanie Nilles: Complicated Woman\nBorn in Chicago, now based in New Orleans, Stephanie Nilles is gifted and complicated: She's a blues-jazz scamp. With 5 full-length albums under her belt and averaging 150 shows a year, this seriously talented saloon-happy singer has hustled her way around the United States, Europe, and Canada. She\u2019s studied piano and cello since the age of six, was a gold medalist at the Fischoff Competition, and performed on NPR on three occasions by the age of seventeen. She\u2019s also shared the stage with Bobby McFerrin in Carnegie Hall. This time she'll be bringing trumpet and clarinet playing\u00a0Thomas Deakin\u00a0with her.\u00a0Here\u2019s a taste\nThe setting is an absolutely remarkable home adjacent Whytecliff Park in Horseshoe Bay where James\u00a0Clavell wrote \"Shogun\". \u00a0Seats are limited.\u00a0The music direct, the groove strong in a Chicago-NOLA gumbo jazz/punk/barrelhouse\u00a0style. SO COME. Bring your favorite drink and a plate of food to share (potluck).\u00a0\nSee you there!\nLionsBayHouseConcerts\u00a02017-2018\u00a0Lead Sponsor:\u00a0Thyra McKilligan of Re/Max Masters\u00a0has been a North Shore resident for over 25 years, but her specialty is Lions Bay.\u00a0LionsBayHouseConcerts\u00a0Supporting Sponsor:\u00a0Longtime Lions Bay resident and ceramics artist Lucy Traini has sponsored our lighting system.\u00a0#GRATITUDE Sustaining Donors:\u00a0Thanks to Jim Fletcher and Elizabeth Holt for their generous financial gifts of support for this concert presentation.\nYour acknowledgement means the world. You make our load lighter. You enable us to bring outrageously talented musicians to local living rooms for intimate experiences. Together we are stronger. THANK YOU!",
            "html": "<P><STRONG>LionsBayHouseConcerts: Stephanie Nilles: Complicated Woman<\/STRONG><\/P>\n<P>Born in Chicago, now based in New Orleans, <A HREF=\"http://www.stephanienilles.com/\" TARGET=\"_blank\" TITLE=\"Stephanie Nilles Website\" REL=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Stephanie Nilles<\/A> is gifted and complicated: She's a blues-jazz scamp. With 5 full-length albums under her belt and averaging 150 shows a year, this seriously talented saloon-happy singer has hustled her way around the United States, Europe, and Canada. She\u2019s studied piano and cello since the age of six, was a gold medalist at the Fischoff Competition, and performed on NPR on three occasions by the age of seventeen. She\u2019s also shared the stage with Bobby McFerrin in Carnegie Hall. This time she'll be bringing trumpet and clarinet playing\u00a0<A HREF=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QEbVcVvfE1E\" TARGET=\"_blank\" TITLE=\"Thomas Deakin\" REL=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Thomas Deakin<\/A>\u00a0with her.\u00a0<STRONG><A HREF=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2hrSr5R53w0\" TARGET=\"_blank\" TITLE=\"Stephanie Nilles & Thomas Deakin\" REL=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Here\u2019s a taste<\/A><\/STRONG><STRONG><BR><\/STRONG><\/P>\n<P><SPAN><SPAN>The setting is an absolutely <STRONG>remarkable home adjacent Whytecliff Park in Horseshoe Bay where James\u00a0Clavell wrote \"Shogun\"<\/STRONG>. \u00a0<\/SPAN><SPAN>Seats are limited.\u00a0<\/SPAN><SPAN>The music direct, the groove strong in a Chicago-NOLA gumbo <SPAN>jazz/punk/barrelhouse\u00a0<\/SPAN>style. <SPAN>SO COME. Bring your favorite drink and a plate of food to share (potluck).\u00a0<\/SPAN><\/SPAN><\/SPAN><\/P>\n<P>See you there!<\/P>\n<P CLASS=\"p1\"><STRONG>LionsBayHouseConcerts\u00a02017-2018\u00a0Lead Sponsor:<\/STRONG>\u00a0<A HREF=\"http://www.thyramckilligan.com/\" TARGET=\"_blank\" REL=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow noopener noreferrer nofollow\"><SPAN CLASS=\"s1\">Thyra McKilligan of Re/Max Masters<\/SPAN><\/A>\u00a0has been a North Shore resident for over 25 years, but her specialty is Lions Bay.\u00a0<STRONG>LionsBayHouseConcerts\u00a0Supporting Sponsor:<\/STRONG>\u00a0Longtime Lions Bay resident and ceramics artist Lucy Traini has sponsored our lighting system.\u00a0<STRONG><STRONG>#GRATITUDE Sustaining Donors:<\/STRONG>\u00a0<\/STRONG>Thanks to Jim Fletcher and Elizabeth Holt for their generous financial gifts of support for this concert presentation.<\/P>\n<P CLASS=\"p1\"><SPAN>Your acknowledgement means the world. You make our load lighter. You enable us to bring outrageously talented musicians to local living rooms for intimate experiences. Together we are stronger. <STRONG>THANK YOU<\/STRONG>!<\/SPAN><\/P>"
